Checking odd variants

There are 2 mutations found in many samples Im making sure they fit the build here. Mainly Im checking to see that they are not being infered becuase of issues in the controls. They are not. The axis is 1-expected frequency because these are infered variants. Note they are found at different frequencies across the data.

Checking coverage

I have found that sometimes we get poor coverage and this can throw us off if we use duplicate sequencing and average the frequency of the variants. Im chekcing the average coverage of each sample here.
